---
import ProjectLayout from "@layouts/ProjectLayout.astro";
import { getEntry } from "astro:content";

const project = (await getEntry("projects", "spectra"))!;
---

<ProjectLayout {...project.data}>
    {/* Introduction */}
    <div>
        <iframe
            class="float-right ml-8 h-44 w-44 border-none"
            src="https://bandcamp.com/EmbeddedPlayer/album=4146003043/size=large/bgcol=181a1b/linkcol=056cc4/minimal=true/transparent=true/"
            seamless></iframe>

        <p>
            <em>Spectra</em> is an album exploring the spectrum of joy that we feel. Mainly split into two parts, it is also
            an experiment on marching-pace music as well as more band-based music. A mix of the old and new, <em
                >Spectra</em
            >
            remixes some familiar melodies from my previous works but also includes some new tunes.
        </p>
        <p>
            Created over several months in FL Studio, I am proud to present this album as the best set of music that I
            have made yet. I hope you'll like them.
        </p>
        <p>
            The final album is primarily available on <a href="https://melodicgluon.bandcamp.com/album/spectra"
                >Bandcamp</a
            >.
        </p>
    </div>

    {/* Tracks */}
    <div class="mt-4">
        <h2>Tracks</h2>
        <p>
            There are two parts to the tracks in <em>Spectra</em>. The first part is called "In The Open" and the second
            is called "Behind Closed Doors". An intermission piece, <em>Lightning Alert</em>, separates the two parts.
        </p>

        <div>
            <div class="music-entry">
                <span class="music-title">March of the Changing Winds</span>
                <span class="music-duration">[01:40]</span>
            </div>
            <div class="music-image">
                {/* TODO: Use image component */}
                <img alt="Banner" src="/projects/spectra/March-of-the-Changing-Winds.png" />
            </div>
            <div class="music-buttons">
                <a
                    class="button bandcamp-button"
                    href="https://melodicgluon.bandcamp.com/track/march-of-the-changing-winds"
                    target="_blank">Bandcamp</a
                >
            </div>
            <p class="music-caption">
                Together we stand<br />
                Along with the changing winds<br />
                United as one
            </p>
            <div class="music-description">
                <p>
                    Serving as the introduction to the album, <em>March of the Changing Winds</em> is a military band inspired
                    piece that provides a powerful entrance with its melody and lyrics.
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div>
            <div class="music-entry">
                <span class="music-title">Our Common Dream</span>
                <span class="music-duration">[04:12]</span>
            </div>
            <div class="music-image">
                {/* TODO: Use image component */}
                <img alt="Banner" src="/projects/spectra/Our-Common-Dream.png" />
            </div>
            <div class="music-buttons">
                <a
                    class="button bandcamp-button"
                    href="https://melodicgluon.bandcamp.com/track/our-common-dream"
                    target="_blank">Bandcamp</a
                >
            </div>
            <p class="music-caption">
                Join us in this song<br />
                Championing this worthy cause<br />
                Believing in dreams
            </p>
            <div class="music-description">
                <p>
                    <em>Our Common Dream</em> is a nice follow-up to <em>March of the Changing Winds</em>, using the
                    same pacing of a marching band/military band song. A reimagining of <em>Gateway</em> from <em
                        >Dreams</em
                    >, the addition of the marching percussion infuses it with more gusto and melody than done
                    previously.
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div>
            <div class="music-entry">
                <span class="music-title">Drapeaux Flottants</span>
                <span class="music-duration">[02:56]</span>
            </div>
            <div class="music-image">
                {/* TODO: Use image component */}
                <img alt="Banner" src="/projects/spectra/Drapeaux-Flottants.png" />
            </div>
            <div class="music-buttons">
                <a
                    class="button bandcamp-button"
                    href="https://melodicgluon.bandcamp.com/track/drapeaux-flottants"
                    target="_blank">Bandcamp</a
                >
            </div>
            <p class="music-caption">
                Symbols of our pride<br />
                Flying high above the crowd<br />
                For all our honour
            </p>
            <div class="music-description">
                <p>
                    Representation matters when we seek to express ourselves. <em>Drapeaux Flottants</em>' cheerful
                    melody reminds us all to respect the symbols that represent us and our honour.
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div>
            <div class="music-entry">
                <span class="music-title">Pour Notre Bonheur</span>
                <span class="music-duration">[03:16]</span>
            </div>
            <div class="music-image">
                {/* TODO: Use image component */}
                <img alt="Banner" src="/projects/spectra/Pour-Notre-Bonheur.png" />
            </div>
            <div class="music-buttons">
                <a
                    class="button bandcamp-button"
                    href="https://melodicgluon.bandcamp.com/track/pour-notre-bonheur"
                    target="_blank">Bandcamp</a
                >
            </div>
            <p class="music-caption">
                Sacrifice plenty<br />
                To obtain our happiness<br />
                A worthy trade?
            </p>
            <div class="music-description">
                <p>
                    <em>Pour Notre Bonheur</em> serves as a reminder of our mission and our sacrifices; to carry on as who
                    we are and to embrace the truth. The purposeful backing of the track mixed with the melodic strings drives
                    forward the passion we have, while the ending is a stark reminder of those we lost.
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div>
            <div class="music-entry">
                <span class="music-title">Steganographic Sepulture</span>
                <span class="music-duration">[01:32]</span>
            </div>
            <div class="music-image">
                {/* TODO: Use image component */}
                <img alt="Banner" src="/projects/spectra/Steganographic-Sepulture.png" />
            </div>
            <div class="music-buttons">
                <a
                    class="button bandcamp-button"
                    href="https://melodicgluon.bandcamp.com/track/steganographic-sepulture"
                    target="_blank">Bandcamp</a
                >
            </div>
            <p class="music-caption">
                To bury in sound<br />
                Evade any suspicion<br />
                Your truth cannot show
            </p>
            <div class="music-description">
                <p>
                    <em>Steganographic Septure</em> takes a step back from the positivity of the previous tracks and expresses
                    sorrow for those who have passed on. Its mournful melody masks messages meant mostly for those who can
                    decipher them.
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div>
            <div class="music-entry">
                <span class="music-title">Remembrance</span>
                <span class="music-duration">[03:52]</span>
            </div>
            <div class="music-image">
                {/* TODO: Use image component */}
                <img alt="Banner" src="/projects/spectra/Remembrance.png" />
            </div>
            <div class="music-buttons">
                <a
                    class="button bandcamp-button"
                    href="https://melodicgluon.bandcamp.com/track/remembrance"
                    target="_blank">Bandcamp</a
                >
            </div>
            <p class="music-caption">
                Recollect their names<br />
                With reverence and respect<br />
                We lay them to rest
            </p>
            <div class="music-description">
                <p>
                    Taking inspiration from the first half of <em>Awakening</em> in <em>Dreams</em>, <em
                        >Rememberance</em
                    >
                    follows up from <em>Steganographic Sepulture</em> with a slither of hope within its soundscape. Its more
                    cheery tunes as compared to <em>Rememberance</em> reflects the hope for the future as we lay the past
                    to rest.
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div>
            <div class="music-entry">
                <span class="music-title">Lightning Alert</span>
                <span class="music-duration">[02:12]</span>
            </div>
            <div class="music-image">
                {/* TODO: Use image component */}
                <img alt="Banner" src="/projects/spectra/Lightning-Alert.png" />
            </div>
            <div class="music-buttons">
                <a
                    class="button bandcamp-button"
                    href="https://melodicgluon.bandcamp.com/track/lightning-alert"
                    target="_blank">Bandcamp</a
                >
            </div>
            <p class="music-caption">
                Seek any shelter!<br />
                Get out of any danger!<br />
                Hide safely inside!
            </p>
            <div class="music-description">
                <p>
                    <em>Lightning Alert</em> serves as the experimental intermission piece between the two halves of the
                    album. With the thunderstorm fast approaching, it serves as a reminder to hide when danger approaches.
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div>
            <div class="music-entry">
                <span class="music-title">Mystères Sombres</span>
                <span class="music-duration">[03:55]</span>
            </div>
            <div class="music-image">
                {/* TODO: Use image component */}
                <img alt="Banner" src="/projects/spectra/Mysteres-Sombres.png" />
            </div>
            <div class="music-buttons">
                <a
                    class="button bandcamp-button"
                    href="https://melodicgluon.bandcamp.com/track/mysteres-sombres"
                    target="_blank">Bandcamp</a
                >
            </div>
            <p class="music-caption">
                Some of our secrets<br />
                Of which we are scared to show<br />
                Shall remain hidden
            </p>
            <div class="music-description">
                <p>
                    Leading the second half of the album, <em>Mystères Sombres</em> incorporates leitmotifs from Sergei Prokofiev's
                    <em>Dance of the Knights</em> to invoke vastness and grandeur while still leaving room for a sadder side
                    to take over.
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div>
            <div class="music-entry">
                <span class="music-title">Winds of Change</span>
                <span class="music-duration">[02:06]</span>
            </div>
            <div class="music-image">
                {/* TODO: Use image component */}
                <img alt="Banner" src="/projects/spectra/Winds-of-Change.png" />
            </div>
            <div class="music-buttons">
                <a
                    class="button bandcamp-button"
                    href="https://melodicgluon.bandcamp.com/track/winds-of-change"
                    target="_blank">Bandcamp</a
                >
            </div>
            <p class="music-caption">
                What was done outside<br />
                Is when we hide our true selves<br />
                Welcome, it begins
            </p>
            <div class="music-description">
                <p>
                    <em>Winds of Change</em> explicitly calls back the melody of <em>March of the Changing Winds</em> to
                    produce a piano-led piece that references the feeling of being in the open in the first half. The simple
                    instrumentation also calls into question how much hope we should have for the future of the different
                    spectra of joy.
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div>
            <div class="music-entry">
                <span class="music-title">Exordium</span>
                <span class="music-duration">[03:00]</span>
            </div>
            <div class="music-image">
                {/* TODO: Use image component */}
                <img alt="Banner" src="/projects/spectra/Exordium.png" />
            </div>
            <div class="music-buttons">
                <a
                    class="button bandcamp-button"
                    href="https://melodicgluon.bandcamp.com/track/exordium"
                    target="_blank">Bandcamp</a
                >
            </div>
            <p class="music-caption">
                Foreshadowing<br />
                Before the event begins<br />
                A façade to show
            </p>
            <div class="music-description">
                <p>
                    The waltz of <em>Exordium</em> prefaces the real event in <em>Chasing Maxima</em>. The slow dance
                    invoked by the tempo hints at the excitement that follows the melody of the waltz, while hiding its
                    true purpose from those unaware.
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div>
            <div class="music-entry">
                <span class="music-title">Chasing Maxima</span>
                <span class="music-duration">[02:03]</span>
            </div>
            <div class="music-image">
                {/* TODO: Use image component */}
                <img alt="Banner" src="/projects/spectra/Chasing-Maxima.png" />
            </div>
            <div class="music-buttons">
                <a
                    class="button bandcamp-button"
                    href="https://melodicgluon.bandcamp.com/track/chasing-maxima"
                    target="_blank">Bandcamp</a
                >
            </div>
            <p class="music-caption">
                Seeking soaring heights<br />
                Pursuing our ambitions<br />
                Finding joy in life
            </p>
            <div class="music-description">
                <p class="-scale-x-100 scale-y-100 text-right">
                    <em>Chasing Maxima</em> calls in the main ideas of <em>Nightmare</em> in <em>Dreams</em> to evoke the
                    feelings when we succumb to temptation. It is enjoyable, but consequences must be borne.
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div>
            <div class="music-entry">
                <span class="music-title">Ergebnisse</span>
                <span class="music-duration">[03:56]</span>
            </div>
            <div class="music-image">
                {/* TODO: Use image component */}
                <img alt="Banner" src="/projects/spectra/Ergebnisse.png" />
            </div>
            <div class="music-buttons">
                <a
                    class="button bandcamp-button"
                    href="https://melodicgluon.bandcamp.com/track/ergebnisse"
                    target="_blank">Bandcamp</a
                >
            </div>
            <p class="music-caption">
                Everything we do<br />
                Has consequences to bear<br />
                Worth our happiness?
            </p>
            <div class="music-description">
                <p>
                    A remastering of <em>Hidden Secrets</em> from <em>7125</em>, the melancholic melody of <em
                        >Ergebnisse</em
                    >
                    serves as a stark reminder of the consequences one has when pursuing joy. Long lasting effects after
                    the short burst of elation linger in the back of our minds.
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div>
            <div class="music-entry">
                <span class="music-title">We Exist</span>
                <span class="music-duration">[03:40]</span>
            </div>
            <div class="music-image">
                {/* TODO: Use image component */}
                <img alt="Banner" src="/projects/spectra/We-Exist.png" />
            </div>
            <div class="music-buttons">
                <a
                    class="button bandcamp-button"
                    href="https://melodicgluon.bandcamp.com/track/we-exist"
                    target="_blank">Bandcamp</a
                >
            </div>
            <p class="music-caption">
                Our kind, being shunned<br />
                Overlooked, overshadowed<br />
                But we are still there
            </p>
            <div class="music-description">
                <p>
                    <em>We Exist</em> is a melancholic piece expressing the hope that an often shunned and forgotten part
                    of society still exists. It is an updating of <em>Gout Nimoc</em> from <em>7125</em> with the sounds
                    and tools available in FL Studio, and I am happy that <em>We Exist</em> has its intended soundscape.
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div>
            <div class="music-entry">
                <span class="music-title">Vers Notre Avenir</span>
                <span class="music-duration">[03:10]</span>
            </div>
            <div class="music-image">
                {/* TODO: Use image component */}
                <img alt="Banner" src="/projects/spectra/Vers-Notre-Avenir.png" />
            </div>
            <div class="music-buttons">
                <a
                    class="button bandcamp-button"
                    href="https://melodicgluon.bandcamp.com/track/vers-notre-avenir"
                    target="_blank">Bandcamp</a
                >
            </div>
            <p class="music-caption">
                Those before helped us<br />
                We work for those yet to come<br />
                For our future peers!
            </p>
            <div class="music-description">
                <p>
                    Again taking inspiration from <em>Awakening</em> in <em>Dreams</em>, the more band-based
                    instrumentation of
                    <em>Vers Notre Avenir</em>, along with its faster tempo, shines a light on how we should strive for
                    our future.
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div>
            <div class="music-entry">
                <span class="music-title">Cette Fierté Cachée</span>
                <span class="music-duration">[05:51]</span>
            </div>
            <div class="music-image">
                {/* TODO: Use image component */}
                <img alt="Banner" src="/projects/spectra/Cette-Fierte-Cachee.png" />
            </div>
            <div class="music-buttons">
                <a
                    class="button bandcamp-button"
                    href="https://melodicgluon.bandcamp.com/track/cette-fierte-cachee"
                    target="_blank">Bandcamp</a
                >
            </div>
            <p class="music-caption">
                Be proud of yourself<br />
                Despite traits to be hidden<br />
                Accept who you are
            </p>
            <div class="music-description">
                <p>
                    <em>Cette Fierté Cachée</em> is the final track of <em>Spectra</em>. Featuring melodic guitar tunes
                    with tempered piano tunes, this track serves as a fitting farewell to the album with its slow pace
                    and calming melody.
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    {/* Conclusion */}
    <div class="mt-4">
        <p>
            All in all, finishing <em>Spectra</em> is one of my proudest moments. Creating 15 tracks in time for June is
            really no easy feat for me, and I am just proud to be able to accomplish it in time and be able to create an
            opus that I will look back fondly on.
        </p>
    </div>
</ProjectLayout>

<style>
    /* TODO: Update */
    /* MAIN STYLING */
    .music-entry,
    .music-buttons {
        display: block;
    }

    .music-buttons,
    .music-caption {
        text-align: center;
    }

    .music-title {
        font-weight: bold;
        font-size: 1.17em;
    }

    .music-image {
        width: 100%;
    }

    .music-image img {
        display: block;
        width: 50%;
        max-width: 100%;
        max-height: 100%;
        margin: auto;
        border-radius: 5px;
    }

    .music-caption {
        font-style: italic;
        color: var(--light-grey);
    }

    .bandcamp-button {
        margin: 10px 0;
        border: 1px solid var(--yellow);
    }

    .bandcamp-button:hover,
    .bandcamp-button:visited:hover {
        color: black;
    }

    .bandcamp-button:hover::after {
        background-color: var(--yellow);
    }

    .sheet-music-button {
        border: 1px solid var(--blue);
    }

    .sheet-music-button:hover::after {
        background-color: var(--blue);
    }

    .musescore-button {
        border: 1px solid var(--green);
    }

    .musescore-button:hover::after {
        background-color: var(--green);
    }

    /* QUERIES */
    @media (max-width: 768px) {
        ol {
            list-style: none;
            padding: 0;
        }

        .music-image img {
            width: 95%;
        }

        .music-list li:not(:last-of-type) {
            margin-bottom: 30px;
        }

        .bandcamp-button {
            width: 125px;
            margin-bottom: 5px;
        }
    }

    @media (max-width: 425px) {
        .bandcamp-button {
            width: 200px;
        }
    }
</style>
